  In Ruby we can use a method called <span style="font-weight: bold;">map</span>. <span style="font-weight: bold;">Map</span> allows us to execute a given <span style="font-weight: bold;">block</span> for each element in an array. <span style="font-weight: bold;">Blocks</span> are instructions, they take in arguments and return values. <span style="font-weight: bold;">Map</span> is very similar to the method <span style="font-weight: bold;">each</span>; they both allow you to execute a given block to every element in the array, but map will return a new array whereas each will return the original unmodified array by default. Here is an example of map with its block: 
