  <p>
  As you can see in the example above, we take an array and use the <span style="font-weight: bold;">.map</span> on it. This allows us to manipulate and return a value. In the <span style="font-weight: bold;">block { |x| x * 2}</span> it is telling it the program to take an element in the array, assign it the the variable <span style="font-weight: bold;">x</span> and multiple it by two. And since we are using the <span style="font-weight: bold;">map</span> method, it does this for every element in the array. So this program would return <span style="font-weight: bold;">[2, 4, 6, 8, 10]</span>.  
